"{\"uid\": \"unionleader.com-opinion-columnists-patrick-hynes-why-the-olympics-opening-ceremony-was-so-dark-article_6dd1f8da-4f6b-11ef-97f7-ef133787f32c.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Cloudy with snow.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 17, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"High 33F.\", \"from\": 18, \"to\": 27, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winds NNE at 5 to 10 mph.\", \"from\": 28, \"to\": 53, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chance of snow 100%.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 74, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Snow accumulating 3 to 5 inches..\", \"from\": 75, \"to\": 108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Snow will taper off and end this evening but skies will remain cloudy late.\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 185, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Low around 25F.\", \"from\": 186, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winds N at 10 to 15 mph.\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chance of snow 100%.\", \"from\": 227, \"to\": 247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1 to 3 inches of snow expected.\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Updated: December 2, 2025 @ 11:45 am        Patrick Hynes  THE ORGANIZERS of the opening ceremony of the 2024 Olympic Games thought to express their \\\"inclusivity\\\" by mocking the Christian faith through a blasphemous depiction of the Last Supper featuring gaudily dressed drag queens.\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 325, \"end\": 332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"score\": 0.9999999997298801, \"rank\": 2.6695797822105723e-10, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 459, \"end\": 468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999999718057, \"rank\": 2.8414322222650673e-11, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The execrable display was titled, \\\"La C\\u00e8ne sur la sc\\u00e8ne sur la Seine,\\\" or \\\"The Last Supper on the stage on the Seine.\\\"\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.780176249235785e-12, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For a short period of time, the organizers attempted to deny that this was their intention.\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But theyquickly backpedaled, issued a duplicitous apology, and acknowledged it was \\\"inspired\\\" by the famous Da Vinci mural.\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 885, \"end\": 893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.556523337601291e-40, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier this month, as part of theNational Eucharistic Revival, 60,000 Roman Catholics attended theEucharistic Congressin Indianapolis to adore the Blessed Sacrament.\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9493458912760512e-16, \"text\": \"Roman Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How providential, then, that we have the gross display at the Olympics, seen by millions, to grant us the opportunity to articulate how important the historic event of the Last Supper was to the life of the Church, and indeed for all mankind.\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To start, though, I hope the Olympic organizers and their apologists understand how paltry their mockery of Jesus really was.\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 5.393676242667708e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Within hours of the Last Supper, Jesus was betrayed, arrested, beaten, tried, and crucified.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1531, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 5.393676242667708e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sneering crowds belittled him as \\\"the king of the Jews.\\\"\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1582, \"end\": 1586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 0.9367589701919036, \"rank\": 0.06751046087697449, \"text\": \"Jews\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His own friends abandoned Him at His most desperate hour.\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mockery was nothing new to Jesus and the earliest Christians.\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1674, \"end\": 1679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 5.393676242667708e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 1697, \"end\": 1707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999778735229065, \"rank\": 2.2126555469567e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is an increasingly familiar reality to Christians today.\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999778735229065, \"rank\": 2.2126555469567e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People should know what the Last Supper was all about.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1824, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Constitution on the Sacred Liturgy of the Roman Catholic Church,Sacrosanctum Concilium, reads:  \\\"At the Last Supper, on the night when He was betrayed, our Saviour instituted the eucharistic sacrifice of His Body and Blood.\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 2052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1871, \"end\": 1892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.9375670831423935e-15, \"text\": \"Roman Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sacrosanctum_Concilium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sacrosanctum Concilium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sacrosanctum_Concilium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sacrosanctum_Concilium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He did this in order to perpetuate the sacrifice of the Cross throughout the centuries until He should come again, and so to entrust to His beloved spouse, the Church, a memorial of His death and resurrection: a sacrament of love, a sign of unity, a bond of charity, a paschal banquet in which Christ is eaten, the mind is filled with grace, and a pledge of future glory is given to us\\\" (SC 47).\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In other words, at the Last Supper, Jesus initiated the final stage of His public ministry.\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2486, \"end\": 2491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 5.393676242667708e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was here that Jesus instituted the Holy Eucharist, giving the Church its most powerful sacrament, the \\\"true bread from heaven,\\\" (John 6:32) his flesh.\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2559, \"end\": 2564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 5.393676242667708e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 2580, \"end\": 2594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.470872117454664e-42, \"text\": \"Holy Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am the living bread that came down from heaven; whoever eats this bread will live forever; and the bread that I will give is my flesh for the life of the world,\\\" Jesus told a skeptical crowd (John 6:51).\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2903, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2862, \"end\": 2867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 5.393676242667708e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He gave us this bread at the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 2904, \"to\": 2945, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shortly thereafter he would die on a cross in fulfillment of ancient scriptures, making eternal life available to all.\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 3064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"No one has greater love than this, to lay down one's life for one's friends\\\" (John 15:13).\", \"from\": 3066, \"to\": 3157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You want inclusivity?\", \"from\": 3159, \"to\": 3180, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Every human being has access to eternal life through the sacrifice Jesus initiated at the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 3181, \"to\": 3283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3248, \"end\": 3253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 5.393676242667708e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Imagine the darkness that consumes the people who mock this reality.\", \"from\": 3284, \"to\": 3352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a great irony, the trans activist standing in place of Jesus at the opening ceremony displays heart hands, the superficial internet gesture of love.\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3412, \"end\": 3417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 5.393676242667708e-11, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this wasn't love.\", \"from\": 3506, \"to\": 3527, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quite the opposite.\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Love does not mock.\", \"from\": 3549, \"to\": 3568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Love does not ridicule.\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Love does not insult.\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Love does not lie about its intentions.\", \"from\": 3615, \"to\": 3654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Love is self-giving, not self-indulgent.\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3696, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are a nominal Christian, or perhaps not a Christian at all, but are nevertheless bothered by the taunting mockery at the Olympics, you should take time to learn about your cultural and spiritual inheritance.\", \"from\": 3698, \"to\": 3912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3711, \"end\": 3728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nominal_Christian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"nominal Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nominal_Christian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nominal_Christian\"}, {\"begin\": 3747, \"end\": 3756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999999718057, \"rank\": 2.8414322222650673e-11, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some recommendations include, \\\"The Fourth Cup: Unveiling the Mystery of the Last Supper and the Cross\\\" by Scott Hahn, \\\"This Is My Body: A Call to Eucharistic Revival\\\" by Bishop Robert Barron, or \\\"Eucharist,\\\" also by Barron.\", \"from\": 3914, \"to\": 4137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4020, \"end\": 4030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Hahn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scott Hahn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Hahn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Hahn\"}, {\"begin\": 4091, \"end\": 4104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6338483592857446e-44, \"text\": \"Robert Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\"}, {\"begin\": 4130, \"end\": 4136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999968740667, \"rank\": 3.126370148702435e-09, \"text\": \"Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Patrick Hynes is the president of Novus Public Affairs.\", \"from\": 4139, \"to\": 4194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4139, \"end\": 4146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"score\": 0.9999999997298801, \"rank\": 2.6695797822105723e-10, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 4173, \"end\": 4178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novus_Records\", \"score\": 0.9999998446746879, \"rank\": 1.5532511448630132e-07, \"text\": \"Novus\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novus_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novus_Records\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He can be found on X @patjhynes.\", \"from\": 4195, \"to\": 4227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Patrick Hynes  I PAID a visit to the magnificent state of Colorado last week to commune with the spirit of my great-great-grandfather David Powell who spent some time there in the mid-19th century.\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4287, \"end\": 4295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\", \"score\": 0.9999999936107997, \"rank\": 6.381077639906756e-09, \"text\": \"Colorado\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\"}, {\"begin\": 4363, \"end\": 4375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Powell_(actor)\", \"score\": 0.9890230050969651, \"rank\": 0.007656249999998893, \"text\": \"David Powell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Powell_(actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Powell_(actor)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was a Pennsylvania farmer who married his sweetheart Martha Ann Cox and dreamed of getting off the farm an\\u2026  Washington, D.C.\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4436, \"end\": 4448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania\", \"score\": 0.9996552890016758, \"rank\": 0.00034254890047878944, \"text\": \"Pennsylvania\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania\"}, {\"begin\": 4483, \"end\": 4489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha\", \"score\": 0.9999949864912363, \"rank\": 4.962697591139055e-06, \"text\": \"Martha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha\"}, {\"begin\": 4539, \"end\": 4555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 0.9877033503275542, \"rank\": 0.012449739760557766, \"text\": \"Washington, D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\"}, {\"begin\": 4539, \"end\": 4549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.358651024934147e-17, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}, {\"begin\": 4539, \"end\": 4555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 0.9877033503275542, \"rank\": 0.012449739760557766, \"text\": \"Washington, D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"THE LONGEST-EVER U.S. government shutdown is finally in the history books.\", \"from\": 4557, \"to\": 4631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4574, \"end\": 4598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_shutdowns_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999964928872596, \"rank\": 3.507124683232343e-06, \"text\": \"U.S. government shutdown\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_shutdowns_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_shutdowns_in_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Washington Democrats put the nation through 43 days of turmoil, jeopardizing SNAP beneficiaries and snarling air travel across the country.\", \"from\": 4632, \"to\": 4771, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4632, \"end\": 4642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.358651024934147e-17, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\"